replyContent: Unfortunately there is a bug in Samsung's home screen launcher that causes all widgets of a paid app to be deleted when the app is updated! The problem is not related to Business Calendar in any way and therefore can not be solved by us! The problem should not occur when you disable automatic updates in the Play Store and update the app manually.

Samsung S8+, Nexus 6P phone, and Nexus 10 tablet -- Business Calendar Pro.    UPDATE SEPTEMBER 30, 2017. I have been using this great calendar app for over four years on three devices.  Works perfectly on all.  I like the direct, simple statements about cost and ads.  Developers who are confident in their product seldom seek to obscure info on the ads and costs.  And do these developers have good reasons to have confidence in Business Calendar -- it is excellent.  The interface is clean and easy to use. But the app is packed with options so I quickly set up Business Calendar just the way I want it. Everything worked and synced perfectly.  Easy email notifications is a favorite feature.   The paid version's Templates is a big time saver. Highly customizable.   Everything about Business Calendar says it's solid and well-designed by folks you have given us a complete product.  Everyone has personal preferences about calendars and tasks, so this might not be your favorite, but the free version will allow anyone to make up their own mind.    My only minor suggestion is that I would have picked out different default colors -- but I just changed them to exactly the ones I like.

replyContent: The option for events that repeat in a two week period is already implemented in our App since one of the first Business Calendar versions! Open the input mask for new events, scroll to the repetition section at the bottom, choose "Weekly", scroll to the bottom again and choose "Every 2 week(s)". It is also described in our application video.

replyContent: Unfortunately there is a bug in Samsung's home screen launcher that causes all widgets of a paid app to be deleted when the app is updated! The problem is not related to Business Calendar in any way and therefore can not be solved by us! The problem should not occur when you disable automatic updates in the Play Store and update the app manually.

Many years ago, I bought a Palm Pilot and loved the simple elegance of the Palm OS and apps such as DateBk.  Eventually, the Palm OS days came to an end and I realized that Android's built-in calendar app was horrible.  BC was the best DateBk replacement I could find and it's worked for me ever since.  In the support forum, the support team often reminded users that they were a small team and I think most users were willing to cut them some slack, but there have been two issues of late that make it hard to recommend the app:  - Users have made some bug reports and feature requests *a year or two ago* and the only response to some of those has been the "we're a small shop" party line.  While I've been fortunate to not directly experience any of the mentioned issues, it's definitely been a showstopper for folks who eventually post, "Got tired of waiting and moved to another app." - Perhaps worse is that since August 2013, there have been exactly zero responses from the support team. I asked if there was another route for folks to post requests and no response.  It's hard to fully recommend an app where there's no known place to dialogue with the developer in case of problems.

replyContent: You can select and deselect task lists in the same way as you can select and deselect calendars. Just use the menu item "Calendars/Lists" and toggle off the visibility of all your task lists and you won't see the tasks any more in the calendar views!

So in love with this app - well worth the $5.  My work schedule varies from week to week (not "every Tuesday" or "repeat each week"), so with google & other calendars I would have to manually re-enter everything, every time.  With Business Calendar I can create templates that allow me to enter my work days and on-call days using a couple of taps.  Also, other calendars can't handle the fact that I work night shift - they display the morning I get off as an all-day event, so if I'm looking at monthly or weekly quick-views it appears like I'm working all day (which is very annoying).  Business Calendar also has lots of options for personalizing (buy the paid version for the most options, the "dark" view looks super cool), and my Galaxy siii syncs seamlessly w/ google calendar, so I always have everything backed up.  I've used Jorte and a bunch of others, Business Calendar blows them all away for ease of use and customization.
Use it for keeping track of days I work and for meetings.

All of a sudden all my personal calendar items disappear.    I go back in, reset the defaults for the stock calender to get them back.  But once again it only lasts till the next sync.  FYI, the settings on my stock calendar to NOT effect the Business Calendar default settings.  I like B.C., but ready to uninstall because of this annoyance.  Any help or suggestions?

I tried Business Calendar on a whim since it was only $0.49 and didn't have high hopes due to the low price.  I'm glad I tried it because it is the best option I have found.  First, the widgets are great.  I love the look and the functionality of them.  It is the first calendar widget that actually scrolled reliably and easily (I'm using Go Launcher which allows for scrolling widgets).  All the other options seemed to read my gestures as something other than a scroll request about 75% of the time.  It also allows you to add a new event right from the widget without having to open the calendar.  Not every calendar widget does.  Secondly, the actual calendar is extremely functional.  It doesn't simply open the stock calendar, but is a fully functioning calendar program as well.  Pressing a day while in month view doesn't navigate way from month view as all other calendar do, it simply pops up all the events for that day.  I'm running out of characters, so I cannot describe all the other great features, but this is one awesome calendar app.  It is well worth the price and it is by far the best looking and functioning calendar app/widget combo that I have found - and I've tried a lot!

I have nothing but superlatives for this app. It is extremely easy and intuitive to use, has lots of options (but none of them redundant or overwhelming), it looks great (finally a useful agenda/month overview instead of a cluttered mess!), and even the touch interface is well thought-out (unlike so many other apps, where it feels tacked on, and sometimes even hampers useability -- not so here). I even use one of the (many) widgets to show upcoming appointments on my home screen (and that's saying something: I typically ignore widgets for the bloat they are).   There are lots of little touches that make this calendar a joy to use. Simple example: setting up appointment times. Where other apps force you to either tap in the entire time value, or use annoyingly labour-intensive +/- buttons, Business Calendar requires the absolute minimum number button presses. Sounds minor, but you'll soon appreciate how convenient (and time-saving) it is.  Give the free version a go, and see for yourself. This is easily the best calendar app in the market.

To all Amazon users complaining about missing updates on Amazon: All updates of Business Calendar are uploaded to the Amazon App Store at the same time when they are published in the Android Market. The reason why you can't find the latest update on Amazon up to now is that Amazon is manually reviewing every application update before they pass it to their customers (this may take up to one week)! So please don't blame the app for the behavior of Amazon and take back misleading comments concerning this issue
